  "body": "This PR does a few things:\n- Marks functions with a non-Rust ABI as nounwind.\n- Catches unwinding at FFI boundary in `extern fn foo() { ... }` functions and aborts. This prevents us from unwinding from Rust code into C code.\n- Adds a `#[can_unwind]` attribute for extern functions. This is for when we know a non-Rust ABI function will have to unwind. Used mainly in the unwinding implementation.\n- Adds a `#[nounwind]` attribute. It is intended for when a function that won't unwind is used cross-crate, but using `#[inline]` is not appropriate. It is currently used for the `oom` function in `liballoc`\n\nFixes #18510\nFixes #18512\n\nr? @eddyb\n",
